CS||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|Watson gave several examples where he felt it was right to cover when second hand had the Queen. However, in general, it is not right to cover when you have the Q and no other spot cards in 2nd seat. This is because declarer often has a guess as to who has the Q and is trying to induce you to eliminate his guess. Of course, if you hesitate when you have the Q, that tells declarer just as much as if you covered with the Queen. |
PG| ***** 162 ***** |


AT|

So, get in the habit of playing 2nd hand low smoothly. For every instance where it costs you a tricks, there will be three or four instances where it gains you a trick. You will note that when I and my expert friends play, we virtually always play 2nd hand low very smoothly.

